China's State Council Information Office on Monday issued the Report on Human Rights Violations in the United States in 2021. In fact, since slavery was abolished in the United States, forced labor has recurred in private prisons across the country. In the eyes of some U.S. capitalists, prisoners are tools for profit and they've therefore run private prisons like sweatshops. Credits: Editor: Yuan Xin Designer: Wang Shiqi Senior producer: Wei Wei Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)